Date: 21/6/2003
Source: Dominion Post
Author:
Vol / Page: F6
Edition:
Quote: Puha toroi is a fermented mixture of cooked puha and mussels.  The pouha (or watercress) is boiled in salt water, the water reserved and poured over the puha and mussels in jars, then left (sometimes with malt vinegar) for up to three weeks.
